{"ts": "2026-06-08T13:38:33.539434+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: 0c57de2aad9ee533046b71c08b56943be304d867)", "id": "lc_be6b1140-8bd3-4af8-bb6e-791c814c5b29"}, {"type": "text", "text": "const { run } = require('runjs')\nconst chalk = require('chalk')\nconst config = require('../vue.config.js')\nconst rawArgv = process.argv.slice(2)\nconst args = rawArgv.join(' ')\n\nif (process.env.npm_config_preview || rawArgv.includes('--preview')) {\n  const report = rawArgv.includes('--report')\n\n  run(`vue-cli-service build ${args}`)\n\n  const port = 9526\n  const publicPath = config.publicPath\n\n  var connect = require('connect')\n  var serveStatic = require('serve-static')\n  const app = connect()\n\n  app.use(\n    publicPath,\n    serveStatic('./dist', {\n      index: ['index.html', '/']\n    })\n  )\n\n  app.listen(port, function () {\n    console.log(chalk.green(`> Preview at  http://localhost:${port}${publicPath}`))\n    if (report) {\n      console.log(chalk.green(`> Report at  http://localhost:${port}${publicPath}report.html`))\n    }\n\n  })\n} else {\n  run(`vue-cli-service build ${args}`)\n}\n", "id": "lc_42d7b645-cb08-40c3-8941-552895d40f37"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "7b0bfe2d-6441-4144-82df-a5123a485c75", "tool_call_id": "call_00_tADboAlJyP5cnX3Vsoff5299", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-08T13:38:43.369932+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on the repository contents, here is a summary of how to work with the admin app:\n\n---\n\n## Local Development\n\n1. **Prerequisites** – Install `pnpm` globally:\n   ```bash\n   npm i -g pnpm\n   ```\n\n2. **Clone & install dependencies:**\n   ```bash\n   git clone https://github.com/HaitaoWang555/vue3-admin-template.git\n   cd vue3-admin-template\n   pnpm install\n   ```\n\n3. **Start the dev server:**\n   ```bash\n   pnpm dev\n   ```\n   This runs `vue-cli-service serve` and opens the app at **http://localhost:9528** (port configured in `vue.config.js`). Hot‑reload is enabled.\n\n---\n\n## Build for Staging\n\n```bash\npnpm build:stage\n```\nRuns `vue-cli-service build --mode staging`. It uses the environment variables from `.env.staging`:\n- `NODE_ENV=production`\n- `ENV='staging'`\n- `VUE_APP_BASE_API='/stage-api'`\n\nOutput is placed in the `dist/` directory with the public path set to `/vue3-admin-template/`.\n\n---\n\n## Build for Production\n\n```bash\npnpm build:prod\n```\nRuns `vue-cli-service build`. It uses the environment variables from `.env.production`:\n- `ENV='production'`\n- `VUE_APP_BASE_API='/prod-api'`\n\nOutput goes to `dist/` with the same public path `/vue3-admin-template/`.\n\n---\n\n## Preview the Built App Locally\n\nAfter building, you can preview the production bundle with a local static server:\n\n```bash\npnpm preview\n```\nThis runs `node build/index.js --preview`, which:\n1. Re‑builds the project via `vue-cli-service build`\n2. Serves the `dist/` folder on **http://localhost:9526** (using a simple `connect` static server)\n3. The app is served under the configured public path (`/vue3-admin-template/`)\n\nFor an accompanying bundle report, use:\n```bash\npnpm preview -- --report\n```\n\n---\n\n## Environment Files Summary\n\n| File                | `ENV`       | `VUE_APP_BASE_API` | Used by            |\n|---------------------|-------------|---------------------|--------------------|\n| `.env.development`  | development | `/dev-api`          | `pnpm dev`         |\n| `.env.staging`      | staging     | `/stage-api`        | `pnpm build:stage` |\n| `.env.production`   | production  | `/prod-api`         | `pnpm build:prod`  |\n\nAll builds and the dev server are orchestrated through **Vue CLI** (`@vue/cli-service` v4), with configuration in `vue.config.js` and project scripts in `package.json`.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 985, "prompt_tokens": 11276, "total_tokens": 12261, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": null, "reasoning_tokens": 366, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": null, "cached_tokens": 10880}, "prompt_cache_hit_tokens": 10880, "prompt_cache_miss_tokens": 396}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_name": "deepseek-v4-flash", "system_fingerprint": "fp_8b330d02d0_prod0820_fp8_kvcache_20260402", "id": "695d9ff3-64e8-4095-8841-e502c3502e44", "finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "type": "ai", "name": null, "id": "lc_run--019ea774-d9c3-7113-a2ad-1625abaebbfc-0", "tool_calls": [], "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 11276, "output_tokens": 985, "total_tokens": 12261, "input_token_details": {"cache_read": 10880}, "output_token_details": {"reasoning": 366}}}}]}}}
